  "deployment_decision": "checkpoint ships conformal_log_cv_trainval: the val-efficient adaptive methods (normalized/CQR) collapse on the shifted worst source, and the shift audit shows no cheap signal detects that source, so the non-adaptive log interval is the only method whose per-source coverage survives. This is a deployment gate decided on the shift audit and reported as such, not a width-tuning step.",
  "interpretation": "Marginal coverage is guaranteed only under exchangeability; held-out sources break it. The honest claim is per-source coverage plus whether any difficulty signal flags the worst source, not the marginal number alone. Here the CrackTree200 failure is concept shift (different width-label relationship), not covariate shift, so sigma/ensemble-std/kNN all miss it."
